President Biden spoke at the East Room, addressing the departure of his Chief of Staff, Ron Klain. The President expressed his gratitude for Klain's service and highlighted their long-standing relationship, dating back to their time together in the Senate. He praised Klain's intelligence, integrity, and leadership skills, noting his significant contributions to the administration's achievements, including fighting COVID-19, reviving the economy, protecting the environment, advancing civil rights, and restoring faith in democracy. President Biden announced that Jeff Zients would be taking over as Chief of Staff, praising his past accomplishments and emphasizing his commitment to building an economy that benefits all Americans. The President concluded by expressing his confidence in Zients' ability to continue Klain's legacy of effective leadership.